commit.message: Set version to 1.3.8.dev
Push version to 1.3.8.
Change version to 1.3.7.dev
Set version and date for 1.3.7 release

Makefile.in: pass user CPPFLAGS, CFLAGS, and LDFLAGS to gac

As in the upstream Makefile.gappkg, and consistent with the idea that
gac should be treated like a compiler, we now pass CPPFLAGS, CFLAGS,
and LDFLAGS to gac explicitly, to later be passed on to the C compiler
and linker.
Push version to 1.3.7

Removed support for GAP < 4.12

Older EDIM releases are available and provide the same functionality
for older GAP versions.

Simplify loading of kernel module

now using IsKernelExtensionAvailable and LoadKernelExtension

Simplify configure and Makefile.in

It is now sufficient to set GAPPATH in Makefile by configure,
the other variables are set in $GAPPATH/sysinfo.gap.

A similar change was suggested by Max Horn.

Make `configure`, `make` more compatible to other packages

- new option `--with-gaproot` for configure
- old `make clean` is now `make cleanlast`
- new `make clean` does not remove `Makefile`
Cleanup and remove some comments in C code

Change path of compiled.h

Suggested by Max Horn, compatible with older and new build system for GAP.

Remove unused file

(file was produced by some old version of gac, accidentally included here)
Fix declaration lines.
Push to version 1.3.6.dev
Push version to 1.3.6
Update URLs to https
Mention improvemnts in build scripts

Update list of PHONY targets, remove default target

The dedicated `default` target seems pointless given that the first
target is default and the target for ediv.so is first anyway.

Rebuild when build system or GAP change

Regenerate Makefile if any of its input changes.

Likewise rebuild edim.so if Makefile changes.

Use information from sysinfo.gap to locate gap and gac

... at least when it is available (requires GAP >= 4.12). If not,
fall back to what was done before, and assume they are in a specific
place in the GAPROOT.
add a generic testall.g file
Use different file to detect old version

Simplify Makefile

This gets rid of some unused stuff in the Makefile.

Push version to 1.3.5
Minor correction to make update on GAP site work
Another edim -> EDIM correction
